We also use ReLU nonlinearity for the reconstruction term as in the original network, since this
will allow the reconstruction Z to explore the same manifold of Z, thus making it easier to find an accurate reconstruction. In Fig.2(d), for example, the linear span of task output vectors {y1, y2} forms the blue hyperplane. Transforming this hyperplane with ReLU and a bias term will result in the manifold colored as gray and yellow, which includes the original feature vectors {z1, z2, z3}.

